[SN]TITLE[SN]
Tesco pleads guilty over Haslingden petrol spill

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Tesco has admitted responsibility for a petrol leak into a Lancashire river.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The supermarket's Haslingden filling station leaked underground into Langwood Brook, a tributary to the River Irwell, in July 2014.
Tesco Stores Limited pleaded guilty to contravening the requirements of an environmental permit and contravening health and safety regulations at Burnley Crown Court on Monday.
The company will be sentenced at Preston Crown Court in January.
The prosecutions were brought by the Environment Agency and Lancashire County Council after 23,500 litres of petrol escaped from the filling station at Syke Street, Haslingden between 2 and 3 July 2014.
